annotation.TEXT: OH, NO!!!
Hi, Yoshi!

There's actually a Thwomp over here that doesn't always show up. Also, you know how I highly recommended that you not go this way? Well, if you really insist, this is one method you could use to go this way. It's painful, though, so bring a reserve power up!
Wait, maybe if I use tool-assistance to help me pull off another glitch...
Oh, and you don't have to wait for the balloon to wear off to enter a vertical pipe. (Is this also true for horizontal pipes? I don't know...)
Now, you can only go so high here, but you can grab a couple of Yoshi coin halves (which still count as full), and then end up hitting blocks they leave behind in the bone.
Also, these backwards orange ? blocks act like slopes going down and right for some reason, and the xxxx-box doesn't seem to do anything, not even play Halo.
Also, don't accidentally get trapped under those ice blocks while you're doing this.
Puzzle for you all: How could I have possibly collected this flower and gotten unstuck? I know a way, and I'll reveal that answer next time!
Now Yoshi can reach these pink berries! Too bad there doesn't seem to be a way to reach those moons... (I can't corner clip my way in like I did earlier, I don't think...)
Okay, now for the secret exit...
Okay, just one more...
I think there may be a way past this though...
D'oh! I keep letting that egg get pooped into the pit!
Oh, and you can pop this fence 109 with the ? block, in case you didn't know, but that's not why I reentered this level again.
Nope. Totally unreachable that way. If only there was a way to get in there...

Also, there's another trapped MOON! Dang it! Oh, and while I could get the secret exit now, I still want to show where the normal normal exit is (the normal exit that doesn't involve what Red Bull gives you).

...Huh? Oh, this hack must've fixed that! I thought I was going to end up trapped in a glitched bonus game room like in the original! Okay, then I guess it's safe to grab the wings here on the first visit!
Now, back to those pink berries...
And there's Yoshi coin number 10, which I believe is the final Yoshi coin in this level!
So, Yoshi's tongue is actually able to reach the interior berries?
I think I'll leave Mr. para89 alone this time (though I could've had Yoshi eat him so I could fly around this room).
Just 28? Bah, it's because I bumped into part of the ceiling there, throwing off my timing. I'm pretty sure it's possible to get 50 there.
Hmm... That ? block to my left looks totally unhittable, but maybe I can solve that problem by making use of a certain glitch again?
Ah, there it is. Now, you can hit it and it'll make the clicky sound, but that's about it.
Ah, but if you take this 2 shell and use it to block clone the P-balloon block to the left...
BARF!
It's interesting how you get that funny sound effect if you're swimming downwards while holding something while the game is lagging.
Alright, it's finally time for that UnderWater Roadtrip, for real this time! I'm not kidding!
And you've got your usual fishy foes to deal with here.
Hey, blurp! Bite me!
Whoops! Overshot and ended up in the wall! At least I'm not totally trapped.
Again, shut up, clock!
There's Yoshi coin number 9, along with part of a midway gate. Just like in "field of koopas2", I think a midpoint was supposed to go here, but it's glitched, so there's no midpoint in this level.
There's a few things in unique castle that I didn't show (including some that were pointed out to me by you guys).
Also, the winner of the naming vote this time is NOT 3-1! Instead, it's various prime numbers! (Voting results are in the description as usual.)
I'm still not quite done here yet, as there's one more thing to show.
So, I'll just smack this fence 127 as I go by...
Also, some bony foes around here might not spawn initially due to the sprite limit, so don't be surprised if you thwack the ones that are present only to find more of them here later.
YEAH!!! It took a bit of tinkering around to find a good angle to get that to work.
Saving Yoshi comes first! But, can I still get the 1-up anyway?
Sweet! Now, to get through the ice block walls with Yoshi, either swim under the level, or just dismount him for a moment while you clear the way.
Now, as was pointed out to me by SuperSupermario24, with these wall triangles, you can just run up to them and jump just as you hit them to run up the wall.
Collect a few purple coins here, and there's the goal!
Not surprisingly, it's a water level. Start by grabbing this block of 36 coins if you want.
Okay, I'm outta here before time expires on me!
Anyway, let's see if I have better luck with this bonus cloud this time...
Ooh, pink berries! Yummy!
Oops... I was trying to avoid letting that happen.
Gee, I wonder how you reach this secret exit. As a bonus, the silver P-switch is totally unnecessary for this, so you can use it on the fishies if you want!
And, here we go again...
To be continued...
Hello, and welcome back to Chaos CompleXX! Today, I'll be going on an UnderWater Roadtrip, finally! But first...
Now, before I go back for the secret exit, I want a Yoshi, so topp of the secret to you!
WAHH!!!
And here's Yoshi coins 6 through 8, along with many more ice blocks, and I'm not going to bother grabbing every last one of the ice blocks.
Also, more pink berries, but too bad I don't have a Yoshi with me...
Awesome, I'm in, using a Yoshi-mounting corner clip!
You're not getting away from me that easily, Yoshi!
Also, I'll pick on this para56179066067 a bit, just because I feel like it.

Now, I could've flown around and grabbed Yoshi coins there this time, but I want to save the Yoshi coin raiding for the main part of the level itself. Also, that counted as the normal exit, but I will still show how to reach this level's normal normal exit.
Well, I'd love to go down please to the level now! But, there seems to be a fish in my way... Maybe Yoshi will help me get past it...
Okay, that's Yoshi coin number 5, so let's not die or otherwise leave this area until I've gotten all of them!
LOL at the trapped silver coins!
Alright, so let's forget about that "unreachable" ? block to the left for now. Instead, let's get jittery with an ice block!
Sweet! Reachable wings! However, just like in the original Donut Secret 1, make sure you've cleared the level first, because... Well, I'll show you.

Also, this ? block contains a P-balloon. However, I want to clone it upwards so that the original block remains untouched, for a good reason. To do that, I'll need to borrow this para43's shell for a moment...
Okay, my happy smile coins don't seem to be getting stuck this time. That's good.
Eat it!
Well, no sense in following the cloud now. Let's go up this pipe.
You can get a power up from these ? blocks here, but one of them seems to be blocked off by a bone...
Oh, yes. I like this cool new much btter colors!
And then, after I reveal the answer to that puzzle, you can all join me in the "house of the damned"! (I'm trying to sound creepy as I say that.)
And there's the ON/OFF block I showed before, so there's no real reason to go any further to the left.
But I can't seem to line it up right here. Maybe if I tried it from another angle...
Though I will thwack that blurp just for the heck of it.
Finally, a place where I didn't have to go at an odd angle to get the corner clip to work! (I still used tool-assistance for it though.)
Once again, into the pipe I go to claim those two Yoshi coins inside...
Well, I already missed some happy smile coins, but I probably would've had a hard time reaching them with these ice block walls in the way anyway.
I think I'll use the left+right trick to speed things up a little bit here. (Be careful not to embed yourself into the right wall though, which I think would be fatal here.)
Okay, that unlocks the house of the damned, but there's one more place I want to try corner-clipping in UnderWater Roadtrip.
Cool! But, what about from the other side?
WAHH!!!
Also, when you're over here, watch your step, or you might fall into this semi-hidden hole on the left...
Oh, shut up clock.
Got it! Awesome!
Let's try that again...
Aha! I had a feeling there was a one-block high passage I could slip through. Now, let's see what's in that "unhittable" block!
Oh, yes! I managed to save both Yoshi and the (totally useless) 1-up!
The one on the right probably had a 31 shell in it, but the one on the left had wings! But, you can't possibly reach them... If only there were a way to actually collect wings here...
You can go up here to hit a message box, and hopefully you won't be followed by a rip van fish... Uh, oh...
Oh, and it works the same on this wall triangle as well.
It'll be easier if I'm caped.
Now, back into the pipe so I can get both Yoshi coins in here again.
And it involves taking a hit, so I'd rather lose my flower and keep my cape.
There we go! It's bonus cloud time! Collect all ten happy smile coins to be rewarded with a 1-up!
Over here, if you were observant enough during the last video (like TheGoomba98 was), you might've gotten a glimpse of a light switch to the left of the Thwomp as I was getting fishboned.
Alright, now first of all, this pink berry is defective. You can try to eat it, but it won't budge. Must just be for decoration (or perhaps it's due to the fact that this is a vertical level.)
Demo count: 12
Can't seem to reach the berries in the middle... Well, let's try eating the two on the right and not letting the egg fall into the abyss this time...
Oh, awesome! The MOOOONNNS here reappear!
Remember this unhittable ? block? Let's see if I can find a way to hit it!
Aw, what? There's like a wall in my way here!

And Yoshi's pooping out an egg while on the run! (And no, I don't get multiple eggs despite eating eight berries at once. However, it is possible to get up to three bonus game clouds to appear at once if you eat only two pink berries at a time.)
Next on the agenda, there are a few sprites in this room that the sprite limit may keep from spawning, as pointed out to me by MrCliftin1 and TheGoomba98.
BLEGH! Well, that didn't work so well this time...
Okay, now over here to the right of the pipe is an ON/OFF block. I don't know what it controls in this level, but you can hit it if you want.
Oh, and for those that couldn't get the wings trick to work in Rosa Perplex 1, doing it here is a bit easier, so you should be able to get a blue Yoshi without too much trouble.
Whoa! Stay away from me, dude!
Alright, now let's go floating around here! (And I'll leave the 2389 shell on the pipe so it doesn't despawn.)
A flower. I went through all that work for a totally unreachable flower. And now I'm trapped. Well, not really. I can still Start+Select out.
Oh, but first, I bet I can reach that one moon with another tool-assisted corner clip!
I'm sure nathanisbored knows what I'm about to do here!
Let's see if I can get all ten happy smile coins again!
YAAAHHH!!! Start+Select!
Yeah, like I'm going to let that bone stop me... If you have Yoshi, you can do... this!
Okay, that's enough of that.
MOOOONNNS!!! But, no! They're trapped! Is there any way to reach them?
Whoa, how'd I cause that glitch without even trying?
Exiting this room normally through this pipe takes you back to the main area, a little ways to the right of the ON/OFF block I showed you earlier.
AAARGH!!! Stupid coin got stuck in the ceiling!
Okay, that was messy, but I got through. (Of course, if I knew the guy was about to fall asleep there, I probably could've waited and gotten out less sloppily.)
You can grab the lowest ice block from this column, but I think the other three are unreachable. (But if anyone knows how to reach them, let me know!)
But, without Yoshi this time. At least I had a reserve flower, so I can still fry the fishies!
However, if you still can't get block cloning to work, there'll still be at least one more chance to get a blue Yoshi without block cloning in a later level, so don't worry too much.
Okay, now as for these pink berries...
